n=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsdown.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: what i think of patch.. please read</span><hr size=1> You know, people are right.  the procs rock.  Of course, snow/flame didn't get the +75 dex the others did (and all of them were supposed to get that, remember?) but that's neither here nor there.  the new procs actually have made me look into getting those two effects where before, I saw them as a downgrade from spirit of storm.  The damage is nice.<br>
<br>
Of course, the proc changes were independent of the pet melee changes (even Rich himself had them separated) so that hasn't been my concern.  What I see with the melee is that they were on the right track.  What we were promised didn't happen most likely because of a typo of mistake in the coding - and there's been a number of other bugs since that patch (which almost makes me wonder what happened, did someone get disgruntled and do this intentionally before being fired/quit/demoted/something? maybe I'm imagining things there...) there had been a number of the bugs that were causing crashes to systems, or exploits (some still are around that do both, true) but they threw out that emergency patch.<br>
<br>
Possibly they have to go through the code with a fine-tooth comb and look at everything, so that they don't need to throw out patch after patch to fix this, who knows.  Could be a change in policy...  Either way, pretty sure that the pets will be corrected in the next patch (which I see coming around the corner here).  Too many of us have asked, petitioned, bugreported, e-mailed, and otherwise contacted Verant over this.  The sheer numbers alone could be one of the reasons they haven't said anything - they don't want to have to repeat themselves over and over to everyone - but rather let us see for ourselves the fix that I'm very certian is coming.  Actions speak much louder than words, you know?<br>
