<br>
First off some people are actually seeing an improvment to pet DPS. This is because the proc is making up for the loss of melee damage. This is very situationally dependant and it really, really depends of what you are killing. The majority of people are seeing a really severe decrease in pet DPS since the patch. <br>
<br>
Verant was attempting to increase the DPS of our pets two ways, melee increase and proc increase. What actually happened is we saw a decrease in melee damage and an increase in proc based damage. Apparently this was not their intent. They had hoped to increase the pets damage output, based on melee DPS, to about what we were seeing when we gave pets non-H2H weapons. The changes to proc damage was to further augment their DPS but again they knew proc damage would be nullified on certain mobs. <br>
<br>
The outcome was less than desirable and I'm sure it will be fixed. I'm also told that changing our pets isn't as simple as changing say a mage's pet. Our work differently and because of this fixing it will take a bit longer. So at this point I guess we all need to be patient and deal with the hand we have been dealt until the change goes in. <p><img src=http://www.mbray.inet.net.nz/sig/bukar_sig.gif>

